    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/1",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Risk theory studies insurance risk models that describe the uncertainty associated with the claims recorded by an insurance company for the losses incurred by its policy holders. From premium and investment income, insurers set aside funds (surplus) to cover such losses. Ruin theory studies the fluctuations of these surplus processes. Classical problems include ruin (low) and dividend (high) barrier hitting times (see <math display=\"inline\">[5]</math>).</p>",
      "page": 229,
      "polygon": [
        [
          74.1873417721519,
          115.42345924453281
