    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/20",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">The <math display=\"inline\">G-S</math> function was first derived in [6] for the classical Poisson risk model, in which <math display=\"inline\">S(t)</math> in equation (1) is a compound Poisson <math display=\"inline\">(\\lambda; F_X)</math> process. Gerber and Shiu show that <math display=\"inline\">\\Phi_{\\delta}</math> satisfies a defective renewal equation</p>",
