    {
      "id": "/page/1/TextInlineMath/8",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">The G-S function has been used also to analyze some financial instruments, such as several types of perpetual American options [7, 8]. As pointed out in these references, the pricing of perpetual options is related to the valuation of equity indexed annuities (EIA), hence the <math display=\"inline\">G-S</math> function can help in analyzing the financial guarantee embedded in an EIA.</p>",
